Create below tables:
Movie ( mID, title, release_year, director )
Reviewer ( rID, rname )
Rating ( rID, mID, stars, rDate )
Description: The reviewer with rID, movie mID, a number of stars rating (1-5) and rating
Date rDate.
A. Exercise on Create tables from Existing Tables (Sub-tables)
1. Create any new table from existing table (MOVIE) with all attributes
2. Create any new table from existing table (MOVIE) with two attributes
3. Create any new table from existing table (MOVIE) with all attributes and the
directors name starts with ‘M’.
B. Exercises on Views
4. Create a View HighRating which contains movies with rating above 3 stars. The view
contains the movie ID and movie title.
5. Create a View NoRating which contains movies with no ratings. The view contains
the movie ID and movie title.
6. Create a View called LateRating which contains movie ratings after January 20, 2011.
The view contains the movie ID, movie title, number of stars, and rating date.
7. Display all the views generated.
8. Execute UPDATE/DELETE commands on the view created.
9. Drop any view.
C. Exercises on Synonyms
10. Create a synonym for any table
11. Drop the synonym
D. Exercises on Sequences
12. Create a table to store product details (pid, pname, price)
13. Create a sequence named seq1 start with min value 1 and max value 100
14. Consider pid to be generated automatically while inserting the details in table. Insert
at least 3 records and show the details of the table.
15. Consider the same sequence and renumber the sl_no from 101. Insert at least 3
records and show the details of the table.
16. Drop the sequence seq1
